%N A101022 Table of numerators of coefficients of certain rational polynomials.
%C A101022 These rational polynomials R(n;x) appear in the evaluation of an integral in thermal field theories in the Bose case. See the Haber and Weldon reference eq. (D1), l. 2, p. 1857 and the W. Lang link.
%D A101022 H. E. Haber and H. A. Weldon, On the relativistic Bose-Einstein integrals, J. Math. Phys. 23(10) (1982) 1852-1858.
%H A101022 W. Lang: <a href="/A101022/a101022.txt">Rational polynomials R(n,x)</a>
%F A101022 a(n, m) = numerator(R(n, x)[x^m]), m=0, ..., n-1, n>=1, with the rational polynomials R(n, x) of degree n-1 defined by R(n, x) := hypergeom([1, 1, 1-n], [3/2, 2], -x/2) = Sum_{m=0..n-1} R(n, m)*x^m, n>=1.
%F A101022 The rational polynomials are R(n, x) = 1 + Sum_{m=1..n-1} (binomial(n-1, m)/((m+1)*(2*m+1)*binomial(2*m, m)))*(2*x)^m, n>=1.
%F A101022 a(n, m) = numerator(R(n, m)) with R(n, m) = (binomial(n-1, m)/((m+1)*(2*m+1)*binomial(2*m, m)))*2^m, m=1..n-1, n=1, 2, ... and R(n, 0)=1, n>=1, else 0.
